\subsection{Biological modules}{

All modules are disabled by default and enabled with a single flag in
the specs list. See the \code{README.md} module table and
\href{../doc/parameter-reference.html}{vignettes/parameter-reference.Rmd}
for the full list with defaults and expected effects.
}

\subsection{Brain architectures}{

Set \code{specs$brain_type}:
\itemize{
\item \code{"bnn"} (default) — Bayesian neural network with Thompson-sampled
weights and REINFORCE posterior updates (Williams 1992; Blundell et
al. 2015).
\item \code{"ann"} — standard multilayer perceptron.
\item \code{"ctrnn"} — continuous-time recurrent network (Beer 1995).
\item \code{"grn"} — sparse gene-regulatory network topology.
\item \code{"random"} — null-baseline architecture for sanity checks.
}

Two further names are reserved for future implementation and currently
error if requested: \code{"transformer"} (self-attention) and \code{"synthesis"}
(symbolic rule extraction from evolved weights).
}

